import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['normal'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    ax.boxplot([data['normal'], data['actual']], labels=['Normal', 'Actual'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature (°F)')
    ax.set_title('How does the distribution of actual temperatures compare to normal temperatures?')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['actual'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°F)')
    plt.title('What is the trend of actual temperatures over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data['day'] = data['day'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['record'])]
    data['record'] = data['record'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    plt.scatter(data['normal'], data['actual'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', label='Normal Mean')
    plt.axhline(data['actual'].mean(), color='green', label='Actual Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between actual and normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

    ax.set_xlabel('Date')

    ax.legend()
    return plt
